I love food and of course , me being absolutely in love with oxtail , had to try this oxtail beef patty with Mac & Cheese . From the moment I took my first bite, I knew I was in for a treat ! The flavors were rich and savory, with a depth that can only come from slow-cooking but the beef patty is the heart of what holds this beautiful concoction together. The curry goat MORE equally impressive( Called the Drake) The meat was incredibly tender, and the curry sauce had just the right amount of heat and spice was so savory ( best I will get the dish with rice and peas) !!!The flavors were well-balanced, also combined with Max & Cheese and sauce that had a perfect blend of aromatic spices that created a joy for my mouth! I m short I loved both patty sandwiches but the curry goat was my favorite and next time I can do it with just cheese and no Mac and cheese ! I love the touch of the sweet plantain on the top and that the store is full of different/imported chips , snacks and drinks ; making even more unique of a deli !

detailed_reviews.review_text: Charged 15 for the oxtail sandwich with barely any oxtail on it at all, the mash potato was stuck together, not hot tasted mushy!

Everyone on social media was raving about the Oxtail Datmacpatty, so of course we had to see what the hype was all about. The Oxtail Datmacpatty is a great concept, but needs some work. It was definitely lacking seasoning & sauce. There were several other options on the menu, but we only tried the Datmacpatty & the fish. The fish could ve been better. Definitely needed more seasoning & was probably cooked too long because the inside wasn t fluffy. Very dry in my opinion. However, The owners/staff were friendly. Great experience. Would I recommend? I Definitely would recommend everyone to try it, but it wasn t worth the hype in my opinion. People must like it because they had a long line of customers, but they were able to get customers in and out quickly, which is a plus in my book.

Id give it 7/10. As a Guyanese, I think some can agree we cook with heavy seasoning, salt, pepper, etc. DatzDeli should create a pepper sauce for those who like spicy to have it on the side. That way for others that dont like spicy, they can still be able to eat something. I think now theyre more out there, based on the reviews.. Quality is becoming an issue. These patties were over $30.. I love the story. If you also know some people dont like to get into business with their family. They are beating the odds. Id love to support this business some more. Hopefully, there are some improvements over time.
detailed_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hello thank you for your review we do carry pepper sauce you just have to ask for pepper on your Patty or on the side thank you for feed back . See you again soon .

Datz Deli in Queens, NY, is a culinary gem that beautifully blends Caribbean influences into their dishes. We recently tried the DatMacPatty, a veggie patty bursting with the delightful combination of warm mac and cheese, spinach, and cheese, all enveloped in a soft coco bread   a true flavor explosion that exceeded our expectations! Additionally, the Drake DatMacPatty, featuring goat curry and baked mac and cheese encased in a Caribbean-styled beef patty, was a taste sensation like no other. The choice of warm cocoa bread elevated the experience, making it a must-try for anyone seeking a unique and delicious dining adventure. The ambiance was welcoming, and the staff provided excellent service. Datz Deli has certainly carved its niche in bringing innovative and mouthwatering Caribbean-inspired dishes to Queens. We cant wait to return for more culinary adventures at this fantastic location!

Nothing to write home about. Or maybe that was just a bad day. Who knows?  They also have lots of interesting exotic snacks from different countries around the world. One Stop Patty Shop DatzDeli, an unassuming deli in the L E S that serves up some of the best beef patties in NYC. The patties are made with fresh, high-quality ingredients and are seasoned to perfection. The crust is flaky and buttery, and the filling is juicy and flavorful. Dat Mac Patty is blowing up at this Gyanese deli in Holis Hills Queens.  @datzdeli190 Theyve  been open for about 6 months and their Dat mac patty has gone viral! A meat patty sliced open, layered with american cheese,  lump of mac and cheese and your choice of oxtail,  chicken, or curried goat. Wrapped up with love into a coco bread and topped with mooore sauce. The oxtail is the most popular and they dish out about 300 a day! The oxtail dish is a family recipie Man, this is one great invention! Layers of incredible flavor  the fall of the bone slow cooked meat, cheese and the coco bread. Damn! Go say hi to the Datz Deli Fam and get a Dat Mac Patty inspired by their childhood food. This sandwich was inspired by the meat patries stuffed with pepporoni and mozzarella sticks in local pizza shops when they were kids. The folks here were super friendly. Brothers Josh and Bobby are awesome. Adele at the register greets you with a great smile and patiently navigates  the ever growing line of folks waiting for the oxtail to be ready. They dont serve it until the meat is falling off the bone. They make everything in-house or in their bakery.
